7/5/00
  Recompile from ytse-sp view:
    dpi1021.fls, statmux1011.fls

  BUG: PPC has problem resetting the DSPs!
  BUG: DSP hang after force switch!

  Checked in latest changes for channel event model

  Got new PPC code mainSeach1.fls from Jinbo which supports RESET.

  Modified splice control task for timeout detection.  After that, the code
  seems to be much stable.  Runs at least for 112 min.
  However, we noticed that there are picture flickering, possibly due to
  buffer underflow.  Tandberg shows that VPTS use to be very low (<10%)
  when flickering occurs.  Then it usually returns to about 30% level.
  Will try to use a higher delay parameter for statmux.
  Changed ACTIVE_THRESHOLD from 20 to 24.
  => statmux1012.fls
  Seems the video flickering is less observable.  The Tandberg also shows
  a higher VPTS use number (>60).  We need to do some more test to verify
  this though.

  Added checking for splice control task in monitor task.  After that the code
  has allocation problem in CRAM.  Moved the .const section into SDRAM for
  testing.

  Seems the code works well with the .const section moved into SDRAM.
  Verified that the .const section contains only printf constants.
  With this modification, you can print whatever you want.
  Checked in changes.

  Make SEAC an configuration keyword.  Checked in changes.

  BUG: from ad back to network, the transit is not clean.  See pictures with
       blocks.  Pattern changes!  Log files say there is no gap in the switch!
  Turning off audio did not help.

  Try increasing ACTIVE_THRES in mux from 28 back to 32 to see whether
  it helps.
  => statmux1013.fls
  Problem still exists.

  What if I turn off sequence end code insertion?


