7/24/00
  Weekend test: system still running.  However, stop switching around Sunday
    evening.  Possibly due to PPC NTP synchronization.

  Issue: When we pull cable during AD1->AD2 switch, a forced switch is
    generated to PPC.  However, we don't know whether AD2 is playing.
    As a result, screen remains blank until trap is triggered.
  Wrong analysis: After the forced switch from AD1->AD2, PPC will think
    AD2 is playing, and issue the next switch request AD2->Live.  The splicer
    should then immediately generate another forced switch and go back to
    the live channel.  So this should be no problem.
  However, I found out that Statmux for some reason, stop sending back
    those dummy pictures back to me.  As a result, I cannot proceed and
    send the forced switch indication to PPC.  This is the real problem!

  Submit DDTS for:
    - Statmux generates too many error/warning message which jam the log file
      and is probably causing PPC to hang.
    - PPC generate lots of repeated DSP debug message around reset point
    - Statmux killed by dummy pictures

  Upgrade to new RC:
    - block.s60, block2.s60: replaced with copies from bitshaper directory
          in the main branch.
    - const.c: added intraCutFreqThreshold and interCutFreqThreshold arrays
    - block.c: VideoEs_getmpg2intrablock(), VideoEs_getmpg2interblock()
          All changes can be found by searching for "#if CUT_HIGHFREQ"
    - rc.h:  Replaced intra/er/CutFreqDepth, intra/er/FrmLevCutDepth
          with intra/er/CutFreqMatrix[].
    - rc.c: same as rc.h.  Also removed used of old variable in rcPicInit().
    - dpi.c: added rcInit() to initialize intra/er/CutFreqMatrix[] to 0.
    Code is compilable and runnable at this point.

    Changes committed.


